{"chunk_id": "cf696d66-f358-45db-be81-115bb64909e9", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 72, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "? Ensure provision of extra food and healthcare to pregnant and lactating women Rationale: /c63Pregnancy is physiologically and nutritionally a highly demanding period. Extra food is required to meet the requirements of the fetus. /c63A woman prepares herself to meet the nutritional demands by increasing her own body fat deposits during pregnancy. /c63A lactating mother requires extra food to secrete adequate quantity/ quality of milk and to safe guard her own health. Pregnancy is a demanding physiological state. In India, it is observed that diets of women from the low socioeconomic groups are essentially similar during pre- pregnant, pregnant and lactating periods. Consequently, there is widespread maternal malnutrition leading to high prevalence of low birth weight infants and very", "embedding": [0.0039474922232329845, -0.045628055930137634, -0.05194174498319626, 0.09948427230119705, 0.008444615639746189, 0.06259384751319885, -0.028599627315998077, 0.06652812659740448, -0.07747545093297958, -0.006176774390041828, 0.028400244191288948, -0.08395161479711533, -0.08272601664066315, -0.10912074893712997, 0.07638903707265854, -0.06720250844955444, 0.07878255844116211, -0.031296778470277786, -0.02547592483460903, 0.015234718099236488, 0.023422377184033394, -0.03238573670387268, 0.05676707997918129, -0.017605453729629517, 0.0494442954659462, -0.08517728745937347, 0.05350546911358833, -0.018683739006519318, 0.020207153633236885, 0.07178855687379837, -0.000357808661647141, -0.008374687284231186, 0.023628009483218193, -0.01134976465255022, -0.09401419758796692, 0.06104777008295059, 0.052635833621025085, -0.020229436457157135, 0.012827521190047264, -0.043623410165309906, 0.023178787901997566, -0.03004103153944